Privacy Policy
Effective Date: 2024/13/3
This Privacy Policy describes how SmallBizSocial ("we," "our," or "us") collects, uses, shares, and protects your personal information in connection with your use of our mobile application ("App") and any related services (collectively, the "Service").
	•	Information We Collect
1.1. Information You Provide:
	•	When you register an account with us, we collect information such as your name, email address, and other contact details.
	•	If you choose to provide it, we may collect additional information such as your business name, business address, and business contact information.
	•	We may collect information you provide when you contact us for customer support or otherwise communicate with us.
1.2. Information We Automatically Collect:
	•	When you use the App, we may automatically collect certain information about your device, including your device type, operating system, IP address, mobile device identifiers, and information about your use of the App.
	•	We may use cookies and similar tracking technologies to collect information about your interactions with the App.
	•	How We Use Your Information
We may use the information we collect for various purposes, including:
	•	Providing and maintaining the Service;
	•	Communicating with you about the Service, including updates and promotions;
	•	Analyzing usage of the Service to improve its functionality and user experience;
	•	Personalizing your experience with the Service;
	•	Responding to your inquiries and providing customer support.
	•	How We Share Your Information
We may share your information in the following circumstances:
	•	With third-party service providers who assist us in providing the Service;
	•	With business partners or affiliates for promotional or marketing purposes, but only where you have consented to such sharing;
	•	In response to a legal request or when required to protect our rights or comply with applicable law.
	•	Data Retention
We will retain your information for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy, unless a longer retention period is required or permitted by law.
	•	Security
We take reasonable measures to protect your information from unauthorized access or disclosure. However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is completely secure, so we cannot guarantee absolute security.
	•	Your Choices
You may choose not to provide certain information, but this may limit your ability to use certain features of the Service.
	•	Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, you may contact us at Smallbizsocial96@gmail.com.
	•	Changes to this Privacy Policy
We reserve the right to modify this Privacy Policy at any time. If we make material changes to this Privacy Policy, we will notify you by email or by posting a notice within the App. Your continued use of the Service after the effective date of the revised Privacy Policy constitutes your acceptance of the changes.
By using the App, you consent to the collection and use of your information as described in this Privacy Policy.

